title: Towards Generalizable Safety in Crowd Navigation via Conformal Uncertainty Handling
summary: Towards Generalizable Safety in Crowd Navigation via Conformal Uncertainty Handling . Mobile robots navigating in crowds trained using reinforcement learning are currently known to suffer performance degradation when faced with out-of-distribution scenarios . We propose that by properly accounting for the uncertainties of pedestrians, a robot can learn safe navigation policies .
